-- Engen to Open 8 Sub-Saharan Oil Distributors, Business Day Says
-- B y   M a t t h e w   H i l l
-- 2012-08-07T07:43:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-07/engen-to-open-8-sub-saharan-oil-distributors-business-day-says.html
Petroliam Nasional Bhd.’s South
African unit, Engen, will open another eight of its branded oil
distribution centers in the region,  Business Day  reported,
citing the company.  In addition to its franchises, known as The Oil Centre, the
petroleum company will set up a further nine lubricant
distribution centers this year under different names, the
Johannesburg-based publication said. Engen already opened The
Oil Centre, which distributes Engen- and Mobil-branded
lubricants, in  Zambia , Business Day said. Engen plans to become
one of sub-Saharan  Africa ’s three biggest lubricant suppliers by
2016, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Matthew Hill in Johannesburg at 
